            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> yes [ad330e9](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/commit/ad330e99d1feed6277fa1a10fb0b333eecf4d5b1) is super old, seems like this should be reported to winget...\n\nYeah. Actually, someone [suggested removing the Nightly](https://github.com/microsoft/winget-pkgs/issues/291460#issuecomment-3270082730) from `winget`, because the Nightly updates every day automatically, while PRs in `winget-pkgs` require human review. So it's probably unrealistic to expect  moderators to approve those PRs every day – the [last commit](https://github.com/microsoft/winget-pkgs/commits/master/manifests/n/Neovim/Neovim/Nightly/0.12.0) was about 3 months ago.\n\nI asked GPT to write two scripts to make it easier to install the Nightly build (I'm using PowerShell 7.x):\n<details><summary>manual.ps1</summary>\n<p>\n\n```ps1\n$url = \"https://github.com/neovim/neovim/releases/download/nightly/nvim-win64.msi\"\n$out = \"$env:TEMP\\nvim-nightly.msi\"\n\nInvoke-WebRequest -Uri $url -OutFile $out\n\nStart-Process msiexec.exe -Verb RunAs -Wait -ArgumentList \"/i `\"$out`\" /quiet /norestart\"\n\n$code = $LASTEXITCODE\n\nif ($code -eq 0) {\n  Write-Host \"Installation successded\"\n} else {\n  Write-Host \"Installation failed: $code\"\n}\n\nrm $out\n```\n</p>\n</details>  \n\n<details><summary>nightly.ps1</summary>\n<p>\n\n```ps1\n\n# enable local manifest feature\nStart-Process winget -Verb RunAs -ArgumentList \"settings --enable LocalManifestFiles\"\n\n$AssetName = \"nvim-win64.msi\"\n\n$Headers = @{\n    \"Accept\" = \"application/vnd.github+json\"\n    \"X-GitHub-Api-Version\" = \"2026-03-10\"\n}\n\n# fetch nightly info\n$Release = Invoke-RestMethod `\n    -Uri \"https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/releases/tags/nightly\" `\n    -Headers $Headers\n\n$Asset = $Release.assets | Where-Object { $_.name -eq $AssetName }\n\nif (-not $Asset) {\n  throw \"Asset not found\"\n}\n\n$Sha = $Asset.digest -replace \"^sha256:\", \"\"\n$Url = $Asset.browser_download_url\n\n$match = [regex]::Match($Release.body, 'NVIM v([0-9]+\\.[0-9]+\\.[0-9]+)-dev')\nif ($match.Success) {\n  $Version = $match.Groups[1].Value\n} else {\n  throw \"Failed to extract version from release body\"\n}\n\nWrite-Host \"Url: $Url\"\nWrite-Host \"Sha256: $Sha\"\nWrite-Host \"Version: $Version\"\n\n# generate manifest\n$TempDir = New-Item -ItemType Directory -Path ([System.IO.Path]::GetTempPath() + \"\\nvim-nightly\") -Force\n$ManifestPath = Join-Path $TempDir \"nvim-nightly.yaml\"\n\n@\"\nPackageIdentifier: Neovim.Nightly\nPackageVersion: $Version\nPackageLocale: en-US\nPublisher: Neovim\nPackageName: Neovim Nightly\nLicense: Apache-2.0 or Vim\nShortDescription: hello\nDependencies:\n  PackageDependencies:\n  - PackageIdentifier: Microsoft.VCRedist.2015+.x64\nInstallers:\n  - Architecture: x64\n    InstallerType: wix\n    InstallerUrl: $Url\n    InstallerSha256: $Sha\n\nManifestType: singleton\nManifestVersion: 1.10.0\n\"@ | Set-Content $ManifestPath -Encoding utf8\n\nWrite-Host \"Manifest generated as $ManifestPath\"\n\n# install\nwinget install -m $ManifestPath --silent --accept-package-agreements --accept-source-agreements\n\n$ExitCode = $LASTEXITCODE\nif ($ExitCode -eq 0) {\n  Write-Host \"Installation successded\"\n} else {\n  Write-Host \"Installation failed\"\n}\n``` \n</p>\n</details> \n\nsimply run `pwsh manual.ps1` or `pwsh nightly.ps1`. BTW, although it's also possible to add a custom source, I don't think anyone would want to try doing that. :)",
